               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t18470816-1939-charge-1" targOrder="Y" targets="def1-1939-18470816 t18470816-1939-offence-1 t18470816-1939-verdict-1"></join>
               <p>1939. <persName id="def1-1939-18470816" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def1-1939-18470816" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1939-18470816" type="age" value="19"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1939-18470816" type="surname" value="BROOKS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1939-18470816" type="given" value="SARAH"></interp>
                     <hi rend="smallCaps">SARAH BROOKS</hi>
                  </persName> was <hi rend="italic">again</hi> indicted <rs id="t18470816-1939-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18470816-1939-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18470816-1939-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="stealingFromMaster"></interp>for stealing 1 pair of stays, value 25<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.; 1 night-gown, 5<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.; 1 pinafore, 1<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.; 1 pair of stockings, 5<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.; 1 night-cap, 2<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.; 1 neck-tie, 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.; 1 skein of silk, 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.; 2 handkerchiefs, 2<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.; 2 printed books, 10<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.; and 1/4 lb. weight of soap, 2<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.; the goods of <persName id="t18470816-name-1169" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-1169" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-1169" type="surname" value="CLIFTON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-1169" type="given" value="CHARLOTTE SOPHIA"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18470816-1939-offence-1 t18470816-name-1169"></join>Charlotte Sophia Clifton</persName>, her mistress.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18470816-name-1170" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-1170" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-1170" type="surname" value="CLIFTON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-1170" type="given" value="CHARLOTTE SOPHIA"></interp>CHARLOTTE SOPHIA CLIFTON.</persName>
                  </hi> When the prisoner's box was searched, she gave me the key to open it—I found in the box a pair of stays, a new night-gown, a nightcap, a <hi rend="italic">pincloth</hi>, a pair of stockings, a neck-tie, two books, and two pocket-handkerchiefs—I have a set of the books—they are all my pro<lb></lb>perty—the maker's name is on the stays, on a printed card, where I bought them—the prisoner had not the charge of my things—she did not keep her box in the room we both slept in, but down stairs—I leave my things in my dressing-room—she could not have put the things into her box, out of the way—I had put the stays into a basket, to be unburned, to be prepared for cleaning—the night-gown was in the wardrobe up stairs, that was unlocked—the stockings were put into a basket, to be ready for mending—she might have got the books out of my parlour, where I slept—the stays I gave two guiness for, but I value them at 1<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 5<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. METCALF.</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Was her box kept locked or un<lb></lb>locked? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Always locked, I have the key at home—she gave it me out of her pocket—it was her own trunk—she trembled very much when I opened her box, and I said, "You no need to tremble, Sarah, if you are honest"—I took the property out before several witnesses—there of them are here now.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18470816-name-1171" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-1171" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-1171" type="surname" value="HARDY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-1171" type="given" value="LOUISA FELLOWERS"></interp>LOUISA FELLOWERS HARDY.</persName>
                  </hi> I was not present when the prisoner's box was opened, but I was when the things were found—I was there on visit, and I went down stairs in the morning, to bid Mrs. Clifton good-bye, and found her and Mrs. Bradley searching the box—I saw the things all taken out of the box.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> Why do you call her Mrs. Clifton? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> I know the lady by that name—I believe she is married—I have not known her long enough to tell you that.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">COURT.</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Were you on a visit? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes, I am no relation of hers, I am married—my husband was not with me, he is in the country—I have</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184708160213"></xptr>
               <p>known Mrs. Clifton four or five months, I cannot say precisely—I became acquainted with her in town—I think I had been on a visit there on day—I was there the whole of one day, and slept there during the night, and in the morning I went into the kitchen to bid her good—bye, and saw the two sisters searching the box—I had slept with Mrs. Clifton that night, and the servant slept on the sofa—I had never known the lady by any other name than Mrs. Clifton—I have not the slightest reason to suppose she is married.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> The articles were not found in the box.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18470816-name-1172" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-1172" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-1172" type="surname" value="CLIFTON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-1172" type="given" value="CHARLOTTE SOPHIA"></interp>CHARLOTTE SOPHIA CLIFTON</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">re-examined.</hi>) Certainly they were, and I heave tow more witnesses that saw them—they were rolled up in a handker<lb></lb>chief in the box—I took them out myself.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18470816-1939-verdict-1" type="verdictDescription">
